us unerwarteten Seite her zurechtzurücken vermag.  aPoop Feminism describes fecal comedy as a new form of female self-empowerment that is becoming increasingly visible in the resonating space of contemporary popular culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aComedy. 0aFeminism. 4aAmy Schumer. 4aFernsehserien. 4aFilm. 4aFäkalhumor. 4aGender Studies. 4aGender. 4aGeschlecht. 4aKomik. 4aKultur. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aMeToo. 4aMedien. 4aMediensoziologie. 4aMedienästhetik. 4aPopkultur. 4aPopulärkultur. 4aRachel Bloom. 4aSelbstermächtigung. 4aSkatologie. 4aTina Fey. 4aUSA. 4aWeiblichkeit. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aAmy Schumer.  aComedy.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aFecal Humour.  aFemininity.  aFilm.  aGender Studies.  aGender.  aMedia Aesthetics.  aMedia.  aMetoo.  aPopular Culture.  aRachel Bloom.  aScatology.  aSelf-empowerment.  aSociology of Media.  aTelevision Series.  aTina Fey.  aUSA.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839451380zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839451380423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839451380/original  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DKUb2020